storyInfo:
Leto, honey drunk, regales Beehunter with tales of her 'glorious past.'
There are some things that the other members of the Ursus Student Self-Governing Group may not know.

attributes.content: Really? Then why'd you block? Save the talk.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Throw us in the ring and I'll have you on the ground in round one.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: How about this, Leto: You gimme another set. You land a good hit, and I give you a prize. Sound good?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Yeah, not bad. More power in there.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Can you teach me that move?!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Oh I can teach. But can you learn?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: It's just throwing your fists around a bit. What's to learn?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: It's a trick I use against those 'bugs' when I'm diggin' out honey. Does good work on the thorny bastards in the ring too.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Oh yeah. Total knockout, every time. How else could it go?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: If you really wanna learn, head outside and dig out some honey. You'll get it quick.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: The Beehunter's an Ursus who fights for her life. But if we're talkin' about the future? My money's on little Leto.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Hehe, now that's what I like to hear.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Okay, break's over, come fight me.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: 'course, if you'd rather take a beating, we can do that too. I'm okay spendin' the rest of our training room time makin' you my punching bag.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Just you wait, Shura. I'm gonna get you this time!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: If you can't hit me with your fists, why not get a weapon?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: C'mon, I have my pride, Shura.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Although, the training room weapons all have safety features. Getting hit with 'em just hurts a bit.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You grab one too. We'll spar.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Plenty of folks in the ring like polearms.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Hum, finally getting serious, are we?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: There's two ways to deal with somebody using a polearm, you know?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: You have——twenty minutes——of time left in this training room. Use your time wisely and prepare the room for use by other operators. Repeat: You have——
attributes.name: Announcement

attributes.content: Runnin' outta time. Okay, let's go!
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Don't chug so much water right after training. You'll get midnight cramps.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: That's Future Leto's problem. Right now it feels amazing.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: How 'bout it? You learn something today?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Never, ever get close to a boxer.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: The knucklers are just there to scare ya.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: I only came at you with my shoulders and elbows. Plus you got safety gear. No way you got hurt.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: But I couldn't block you at all, Shura.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: What kind of training did you do to get so fast? You have to teach me.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I fought a lot, I didn't die. Ta-dah.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Take enough beatings and you'll learn how somebody's gonna wanna come at you.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: And if you don't, you get dumpstered pretty quick.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: What about me? Am I dumpstered?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You've got me and your sisters lookin' out for you. You ever end up in a dumpster, we'll come fish you out.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: You say that like I'm garbage.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hahaha. Don't sweat it, Leto. You're still a kid. Get some experience under your belt and you'll be a lot stronger. No question.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: (Muttering) I even stood up to Reunion.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: (Quietly) Why haven't I heard this before? You're not makin' it up, are ya?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: How about this? Let's go wash up, get something to eat, make ourselves comfortable, and I'll tell you the whole story.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Sounds good. I asked Logistics to make me up a honey drink a couple days ago. Perfect timing.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: And Dur-nar, I hear she did up some wild snacks the other day. Word on the street is she'll sell you some if you give her the password.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Okay. See you back at the dorm.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: (Quietly) What's the password? It was always Gummy and Her Worship who did stuff like this. I dunno how.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Oh, come here, I'll tell ya.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: (Quietly) Listen up. I'm only gonna say it once. Don't ask questions.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: (Quietly) Dur-nar's Snack Network covers all of Rhodes Island. But for security, you can only get access by invitation from somebody the network trusts. I usually work through Haze. She's hella discreet.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: (Quietly) You knock six times. Long, short, long, long, short, long. Get it?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: (Quietly) Then you make conversation when they open the door. When they say the word 'glockenspiel,' you gotta immediately reply, 'this one's pretty good.' Then you'll get the price and you're golden.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: (Quietly) Don't forget: 'Glockennnspiel,' long in the middle, short at the end.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: I gotta go through all that just to get some snacks?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: That's a pain in the ass. I'll just get Gummy to do it.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Shura, I got the——Hey, you started drinking already!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I got bored waiting for you. But I bought lots. Why can't I do a little pregaming?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Yeah all right. I actually nibbled on the snacks a bit on my way back. They're good.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You think the Beehunter would stand for less?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: C'mon, let's eat, play a hand or two to warm up, and then you tell us about your big adventure.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: You always have shitty luck at cards.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: We're only three or four cans in, and this is non-alcoholic.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: You must be drunk on honey just like me!
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Yeah! And it's hittin' you a lot harder than it hits me.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: And here I thought I was the only one who got honey drunk. Heh, hahahaha!
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: What're you talking about? The great and mighty Leto would never get *hic* drunk!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Yes, yes, God-Empress Leto. All hail! Hahahahaha!
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: What are you laughing at? If we're done with the cards then get over here and listen to the story of Leto the Great.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Yes, Your *snicker* Majesty, Leto the Great. Hehe.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Listen well, Bee——Beehunter. The G-great One speaks.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Right, let's start from the beginning!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I'm havin' way too much fun today. I gotta record this.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: To get the Great One something to wet her whistle!
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Me. Gummy said you sent her to get snacks. I'm here for my cut.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: What? Is there something on the Great... err, my face?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Oh, honey? N- no. Don't be silly.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Oh Mighty Leto——I've brought your refreshments.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Beehunter, come. Let me ask you something.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: And it's hittin' her way harder than it ever does me. She's supposed to be telling me some story about her adventures before.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: You wanna listen in too? Or I could just record it for ya.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: I gotta——nng, I gotta tell her my glorious war stories——
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Yeah, sure, you can have her.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: I'm out. Have a good time, Leto.
attributes.name: Zima

attributes.content: C'mon, Leto. Stop standin' in the door makin' a fool of yourself.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Fine, fine. Leto the Great and Mighty, get inside already.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Um, well, I'm sorry to bother you so late. But, if it wouldn't be too much trouble, do you think you could have your conversation inside your room?
attributes.name: Mousse

attributes.content: That's exactly what I wanna doooooo.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I am so sorry about the noise. Lemme just close our door there.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Sure, why not? Go big or go home.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Oh, huh. Then I guess I better hike up my skirt and start again.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: But I should probably drink something first.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I could go for another ice soda.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: If only that gang of nobles hadn't taken apart the vending machine.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Somebody else thinks they can make it out of the campus?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: The masked dudes just pushed 'em back in. Tsk.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Hey, aren't you Rosalind from class 3?
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: We're from the Peterheim Benevolent Society. Our boss, Big Andrey, wants you to join us.
attributes.name: Student B

attributes.content: How about it? Give it some thought?
attributes.name: Student B

attributes.content: Are you really turning us down?
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: In the past two days, like four or five different gangs have tried to poach me?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I don't even get why we have so many little groups. And they all have such big, tough names.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Huh? What's that supposed to mean...?
attributes.name: Student B

attributes.content: Rosalind, there's kids from a whole bunch of different schools here now. Even a bunch from a noble school got sent to ours.
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: You know how many of our classmates get pushed around by those noble pricks.
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: Isn't it time for us all to band together?
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: Andrey says as long as you come along, he'll treat you right.
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: You'll have food, drinks, anything leftover can go to you too.
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: Okay, I agree to your terms.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Awesome! Thanks for being so reasonable!
attributes.name: Student B

attributes.content: Hold on a sec. Don't get too excited.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: You gotta get me what I want.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Find Sonya and get her to ask me to join.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: That's all you gotta do, and I'll wear your armband.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: We need to think this one over.
attributes.name: Student A

attributes.content: I deal with these boring punks every day.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Come on, did I drink that much just now?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: This is way more fun than talking!
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I never had these before. Always too lazy to deal with the shell.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Mm, I never knew these nuts were so good.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: So that means it wasn't just kids from your school in there already?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: They took students from a bunch of different nearby schools and locked them in with us.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Including the gopniks from Her Worship's school.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Sorry, which one are you talking about there?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Oh, that's Natalya. One of the Ursus girls with us.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I just got used to calling her that.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: She's not a bad girl. But back then she was into some real messed up shit.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Hey, Beehunter, do the thing for me again.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: That trick where you crack the nuts with your hands.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You all suck at putting out fires, but you sure are good at stealing.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I don't have any food here either. Why are they always coming at me?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: They're all gopniks from our school.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: None of these punks have armbands. How am I supposed to know if they're with Andrey or Vasily?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I'll take a few bits, just to fill my stomach.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I can't keep going like this. They bug me every night.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: The garbage from #4 took over the cafeteria cold storage, and the other canteen went up in smoke.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Drinks are gonna be the least of my problems if this keeps up. I won't have food or water.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: What if I went to Sonya?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: She's already got a couple kids over there, right?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: She won't mind taking one more.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Yeah, that's it. That could work.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I offer up a few cans and she'll let me right in.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: That'll be a little more 'stable' at least.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Never would've thought the world's second strongest would have to go beg first place for help.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: But I'd be able to get a good night's sleep over there...
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Hey, Sonya, are you here? I wanna talk to you.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I, uh, didn't mean... I just wanted to, err, I want to join you.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: The ones slumped up against the wall. Take them out for me.
attributes.name: Sonya

attributes.content: I have to guard this place. I'm protecting them. I can't leave.
attributes.name: Sonya

attributes.content: I brought you a few cans. They're yours.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Did you fall in, Shura? Who takes that long in the bathroom?!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Your face is all red too.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Look at you, you can barely talk anymore.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: What?! I've still got a story to tell.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Fire? What fire? Where's the fire?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Oh, oh yeah. Now I remember.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: That life-sized Ursus doll you got, you think you can let me hug her tonight?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Sure. You can have her right now.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: Woah, don't throw her! I can't catch like this!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Heh. Is that all you got?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Get up, Andrey. Where'd all your big talk go?!
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Well, at least you won't be hungry.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Okay, that's the boss down. Anybody else...?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: *Cough*, all right, so you can fight dirty.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: You think I take one hit to the back of the head and go down like in the movies?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Guess this is my food now.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Naw, we're a team. It's what I'm here for.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: And look, she isn't in great shape right now.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: So it's up to me, as Peterheim's second strongest, toAAAAAAaaaaghh that hurts!
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: Just a little bit longer. Almost done.
attributes.name: Lada

attributes.content: That Youth Scout training comes in handy, huh?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: The world's running out of good people. Lucky to have you.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: If that cop had run into kids like you, things would've turned out different.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: (We don't have enough food. Don't have enough people.)
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: (Both the food stores are gone. There's just not enough to eat.)
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: (What if a gang shows up to our door someday?)
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: (I guess I could go talk to the mask dudes?)
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: (No way. What if they turn me into one of those rock-covered monsters?)
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: (I might as well give it a shot.)
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: We don't have much left in the way of rations. I'm gonna go out for more tonight.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: You can't. You're hurt. If you go out again you'll——
attributes.name: Anna

attributes.content: I'm tough. I can handle it.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I won't go far. And I won't take anyone's last bite.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: It's been so long since I've come here. I'm kind of excited.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: This is my old dorm. Why can't I go in?
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: If I was afraid to die, I'd try to find a way out of the school. No reason to come here.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I'm Rosalind, and I wanna talk to your leader.
attributes.name: Rosalind

attributes.content: I'm scared. Scared to death. But my mouth is still going.
I feel like I'm staring into the mouth of hell for the sake of my own pride.
Why did I think it was a good idea to meet the leader of Reunion again?
Was it because I'd say a few words to him and he'd let us all go, or give us food?
Or was I gonna threaten him?
And then the little white-haired kid with the creepy smile said a few things to me and let me go.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Something like, 'your suffering has only just begun' or 'enjoy life' or whatever.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: How was I supposed to understand?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Then he let me go, just let me go.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I went back to the classroom and slept for a while. The next day, the mask dudes were gone.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Things didn't get better after that.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: We thought life in the school was rough.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: When we got out, we realized that was just the appetizer.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Those stories, they'll eat you alive.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: And here you said, you said I was honey drunk. You're the drunk one!
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Cam't benieve it. You just fall ashleep without saying anything.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Beehunter's asleep, so you get to hear the rest of my story.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I got so, sho mush to say.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: You're gonna ask me what happened?
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: You guzzled honey drink until you were dead drunk, then you stole my big doll, collapsed on top of her, and drooled out everything you drank.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: You didn't toss her to me?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I'm gonna take out the garbage. You get cleaning.
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: I'm out. Don't forget afternoon class!
attributes.name: Beehunter

attributes.content: What did I say to her yesterday?
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: That's why I woke up so refreshed today.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Gotta clean up, have breakfast, then find somebody to help me wash this big girl.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: I'll see about drinking with Beehunter again in a couple days.
attributes.name: Leto

attributes.content: Might as well strum a few chords.
attributes.name: Leto
